ica for another family (Molossidae), and a complex diversification process, involving two centres of diversification, for at least two of the families of the Noctilionoidea (Mormoopidae and Phyllostomidae) and possibly for the Emballonuridae. The recently identified Panamanian Realm (including southern Mexico and Central America) seems to have played a significant role in the diversification of New World bats.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Arita, H\u00e9ctor T.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Vargas\u2010Bar\u00f3n, Jimena", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Villalobos, Fabricio", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["american biotic interchange", "biodiversity", "biogeography", "chiroptera", "diversity gradient", "evolution", "molecular phylogeny", "niche conservatism", "phyllostomidae", "range size", "Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/72790b10b5cbada8902c7c7bbaa1b546", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/d3fac382ef5fb107e2c8e3665c7a1baf10f38eab354933d0132e3bbfb48eafad", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/K4RJPGDU", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/K4RJPGDU", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/715848fefcfa1e108bced550c6fd26c2!/b306696-309156", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}